comments.text:
Joke's on Troy Morrison... That's not Barack Obama at the end. It's Joel 
Jackson. He went on become president while Troy stayed in the past, 
dwelling on his short-lived fame, which crashed and burned after he was 
unable to come up with anything remotely funny. In a gesture of pity, and 
to prove that he had made peace with the betrayal of many years ago, 
President Jackson plays along with Morrison's denial, the latter of whom 
truly believing himself to be funny, and awards him with a medal that holds 
no actual value. Troy still wears his high school uniform because that's 
all he has left, and the only remaining treasure he has is a cheaply made 
T-Shirt that reminds him of his brief success. Upon receiving the 
superficial award, he is filled with gratitude, and hands his only 
possession to his old friend. He has nothing left.﻿
